| ASYNC_CONTACT                  | SIG        | List of contact moment timestamps. In the case of asynchronous communication platform enter a tuple of USER_ID of user sending message and timestamp in the same format as DATE.                                                              |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| U_ID                           | PI         | User ID. Tuple of two 6 random integer numbers that are unique ID's referring to a single user. The first ID representing the one that initiated the play request. If the request has not been accepted, only DATE and USER_ID is filled.     |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| GAME_ID                        | SIG        | Game ID. Integer number between [0,n] where n in the total number of games ($n=5$ for this validation study). Integer is corresponding to current game being played.                                                                          |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| SESSION_DUR                    | SIG        | Session duration in seconds. From initiation where both players are in the same game session until one of them leaves.                                                                                                                        |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| GP_DUR                         | SIG        | Game Performance, duration of game. Time (in seconds) it takes  to finish the game. (/NOTE/: this is different then SESSION_DUR as participants may want to keep talking before entering a new game.                                          |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| GP_SCORE                       | SIG        | Game Performance, score of both players. This is a tuple with two floating point numbers. Person that initialized the game is represented first.                                                                                              |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| C_EXP                          | SIL, SI    | MC question: Hoe was uw ervaring met het spelen met deze persoon?                                                                                                                                                                             |
|                                |            | 1: Erg negatief. 2: Negatief. 3: Neutraal. 4: Positief. 5: Erg positief.                                                                                                                                                  |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| C_COMM                         | SIL, SI    | MC question: Hoe goed kon u praten met deze persoon?                                                                                                                                                                     |
|                                |            | 1. Erg slecht. 2. Slecht. 3. Neutraal. 4. Goed. 5. Erg goed.                                                                                                                     |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| C_RET                          | SIL, SI    | MC question: Hoe waarschijnlijk is het dat u weer met deze persoon zou willen spelen?                                                                                                                                                         |
|                                |            | 1. Zeer onwaarschijnlijk. 2. Waarschijnlijk niet. 3. Misschien. 4. Waarschijnlijk. 5. Heel erg waarschijnlijk.                                                                                                                                |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| *Explanation of abbreviations* |            | SI: For measure of Social Interaction, AC: Accounting variable, SIG: Social interaction specific for gaming session, SIL: Needed for measuring social interaction as taken from the SN-LASA, MC: Multiple Choice question, OQ: Open question. |
|--------------------------------+------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|


